Who we are
At
Game Pixels Studio
, we are dedicated to providing an exceptional gaming experience while prioritizing your privacy. Our team is committed to transparency and strives to uphold the highest standards of data protection.
Comments
When visitors leave comments on our site, we collect the data shown in the comments form, along with the visitorâ€™s IP address and browser user agent string to help detect spam. This information allows us to maintain the quality of discussions and prevent misuse of our platform.
Media
If you upload images to our website, we recommend avoiding images with embedded location data (EXIF GPS) as visitors can download and extract that information. By doing so, you can help protect your privacy and the privacy of others depicted in your media.
Cookies
Our website uses cookies to enhance user experience and analyze site traffic. You can manage cookie preferences through your browser settings, and you can choose to disable cookies, although this may affect your experience on our site.
Who do we share your data with?
We do not sell or share your data with third parties without your consent, except for trusted partners who assist us in operating our website and conducting our business. These partners are obligated to protect your information and use it solely for the intended purposes.
How long will we retain your data?
We retain comments and associated metadata indefinitely to recognize and approve follow-up comments automatically. This policy helps us maintain an engaged community while ensuring that relevant discussions remain accessible.
What rights do you have over your data?
You have the right to request access to, correction of, or deletion of your data stored on our site. We encourage you to exercise these rights to ensure that your information remains accurate and up-to-date.
Where your data is sent
Visitor comments may be checked through an automated spam detection service, ensuring the security and integrity of our community. This process helps us filter out harmful content while safeguarding your personal information.